    "faq_nlr2": {
      "type": "nuracom-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "fq_1": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How fast does it actually dry clothes?",
            "answer": "<p>Drying time depends on the fabric, load size, and ambient conditions, but most users report their clothes are dry within 3–6 hours — compared to 24–48 hours on a passive rack. The Stratos model with 6 turbo fans cuts this further to approximately 2–4 hours for typical loads. This is genuinely transformative compared to traditional indoor drying.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "fq_2": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will it work with my ceiling type?",
            "answer": "<p>Nuracom systems are compatible with standard plasterboard, timber, and concrete ceilings — which covers the vast majority of Australian homes. The mounting brackets are included with every purchase, and our installation guide covers all common ceiling types. If you're unsure, our support team can advise before you buy.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "fq_3": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How much weight can it hold?",
            "answer": "<p>The Breeze holds up to 30kg, the Aero up to 35kg, and the Stratos up to 40kg of wet laundry. To put that in context, a full washing machine load of wet clothes typically weighs 8–12kg. So even the Breeze can handle 2–3 full loads at once. The obstruction sensing system also prevents overloading.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "fq_4": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is it noisy?",
            "answer": "<p>No. Nuracom uses ultra-silent motors specifically engineered to operate below conversational volume. You can run it while watching TV, sleeping, or working from home without noticing it. This was a non-negotiable design requirement for us — a noisy drying system defeats the purpose of home convenience.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "fq_5": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do I really not need a tradesperson to install it?",
            "answer": "<p>Correct. The system plugs into a standard Australian power outlet — no electrician required. The ceiling mount uses standard bracket fixings (included). If you've ever put up a curtain rod or a shelf, you have the skills needed. Most customers complete installation in 20–30 minutes. We also include a detailed video walkthrough with every purchase.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "fq_6": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What if I'm not happy with it or something breaks?",
            "answer": "<p>We want you to be completely satisfied. Nuracom offers comprehensive warranty coverage (up to 5 years on the motor) T&C apply, available on our website. We pride ourselves in providing responsive Australian customer support. If you have any issues, our team is available to help troubleshoot or arrange service. We stand behind our products because we know they work.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        }
      },
